From a4ecd069dd44f296d877f82e0992149cbcc76fff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 17:48:21 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] 8.3: regenerate sprites.sif with 8.3-compliant sheet paths
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8 LFN-Option-B execution (task #28), companion to 0033 source
renames + 0034 data-file renames. NXEngine-evo's sprites.sif binary
embeds 64 sprite-sheet path strings (length-prefixed) in its
SIF_SECTION_SHEETS section. Eight of those paths violate DOS 8.3:

  ArmsImage.pbm       -> ArmImg.pbm
  ItemImage.pbm       -> ItmImg.pbm
  StageImage.pbm      -> StgImg.pbm
  Npc/NpcBallos.pbm   -> Npc/NpcBalls.pbm
  Npc/NpcIsland.pbm   -> Npc/NpcIslnd.pbm
  Npc/NpcPriest.pbm   -> Npc/NpcPrst.pbm
  Npc/NpcStream.pbm   -> Npc/NpcStrm.pbm
  Stage/PrtAlmond.pbm -> Stage/PrtAlmnd.pbm

The new scripts/rename-sif.py rewrites the binary in place:

  - Parses the 2FIS magic + 1-byte nsections + 9-byte index entries
    (type, offset, length) per
    vendor/nxengine-evo/src/siflib/sifloader.cpp.
  - Decodes the SIF_SECTION_SHEETS string array (1-byte Pascal length
    + ASCII bytes) per sectStringArray.cpp.
  - Applies the rename map.
  - Re-encodes SHEETS at the new (smaller) size.
  - Recomputes index-table offsets so subsequent sections stay packed
    contiguously.

The rewriter is round-trip-validated: scripts/rename-sif.py --check
produces a byte-identical output for an unchanged input, proving the
decoder/encoder pair preserves the format faithfully. Applying the
rename map shrinks the file from 59482 to 59465 bytes (17 bytes
saved across the 8 renamed strings).

Three caveats worth flagging:

  - Mod compatibility: any existing Cave Story mod that ships its
    own sprites.sif with the canonical long names will load wrong
    sheets after this patch. Mitigation deferred to task #10 (mod
    stretch) — option for a runtime fallback ResourceManager layer.

  - User-extracted Cave Story content (Npc/*.pbm, Stage/Prt*.pbm)
    is renamed via instructions in docs/ASSETS.md, NOT this patch.
    Users running with un-renamed user data will see "could not
    open" errors at sprite-load time despite the .sif having the
    new paths.

  - Credit.tsc (data file, encrypted) may reference credit*m.bmp by
    name via TSC opcodes. Source-side credits.cpp:281 has been
    renamed (patch 0033) and the .bmp files have been renamed (patch
    0034), so the runtime path generation is consistent. If a TSC
    opcode literally references the old path, that would only
    manifest during the credits sequence — verify post-Phase-8 in
    the long-running stability gate.

Why DOS needs this: only DOS without an LFN driver enforces 8.3 at
the filesystem layer. Desktop builds see no functional change — the
sprites.sif path strings are passed verbatim to fopen which resolves
both old and new.
